<subSubSection id="9774E5ECACFB439512FDD16673DD1C83" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="note">
<paragraph id="24255D617717DAD4CD07499BCE592147" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="83FA3FD104DD4F3C8E949866458BE9C3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName id="34211EF7738F3D5B8E89B1FF5F8CCDBE" authorityName="Gregorio &amp; J. A. S. Costa" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Begonia delicata" order="Violales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="delicata">
<emphasis id="4FACFA70B1435822703A11A4CCFE7EC9" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Begonia delicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="32C70025B9DA5BEC0CE3D4747BADD889" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Begonia alchemilloides" order="Violales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alchemilloides">
<emphasis id="4900469CF7938CD15ECAE28F44737558" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Begonia alchemilloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
A. DC., differing by the presence of a ring of trichomes at the apex of the petiole, stipules and first order bracts with entire margin (vs. laciniate) and staminate flowers with 2 (vs. 4) tepals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
